# The one OpenAI call (agent-requested)

This is the "Agent Requested" rule type: it has a `description` (and no `globs`), so the agent reads
the description and decides whether to pull the rule in. Invoked for model-call work.

- Make **exactly one** `client.chat.completions.create(...)` call per request, with a **30-second
  timeout** and **at most one** bounded retry on a transient network error.
- Model is `gpt-5.5`. Build messages as a system prompt + the user's text; fold `max_words` into the
  system prompt as a soft target (default 150, range 1–1000).
- Read the API key from `OPENAI_API_KEY` in the environment. Never hard-code, return, or log it.
- On any provider error or timeout, raise `SummarizerError` (text-free message) so the boundary maps
  it to a **502** — never retry unbounded, never swallow into a 200.
- Never put the caller's text into a log line, a trace, or an exception message.
